<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">Social learning is implemented as follows. Each individual samples other members of the population at a fixed rate 
 <italic class="italic">κ</italic>. If ‘individual A’ samples ‘individual B’ and B’s strategy has a higher payoff that of A, then A will switch to B’s strategy with a probability proportional to the difference in payoffs. Thus if there are 
 <italic class="italic">x</italic> mitigators in the population, the rate at which a non-mitigator encounters a mitigator is 
 <italic class="italic">κx</italic>. Should there be a utility gain in switching (
 <italic class="italic">e</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">M</italic>
 </sub> &gt; 
 <italic class="italic">e</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">N</italic>
 </sub>), the non-mitigator will switch their strategy with a probability proportional to the payoff difference, 
 <italic class="italic">e</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">M</italic>
 </sub> − 
 <italic class="italic">e</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">N</italic>
 </sub>. Since there are a total of 1 − 
 <italic class="italic">x</italic> non-mitigators in the population, the total rate at which non-mitigators switch to being mitigators is 
 <disp-formula id="pcbi.1007000.e004" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1007000.e004.jpg" id="pcbi.1007000.e004g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M4" class="math">
    <mtable displaystyle="true" class="mtable">
     <mtr class="mtr">
      <mtd columnalign="right" class="mtd">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <msub class="msub">
         <mi class="mi">r</mi>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">N</mi>
          <mo class="mo">→</mo>
          <mi class="mi">M</mi>
         </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo class="mo">=</mo>
        <mi class="mi">κ</mi>
        <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width="2pt" class="mspace"/>
        <mtext class="mtext">max</mtext>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">{</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">e</mi>
          <mi class="mi">M</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">e</mi>
          <mi class="mi">N</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">,</mo>
         <mn class="mn">0</mn>
         <mo class="mo">}</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">.</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
    </mtable>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(3)</label>
 </disp-formula> Using similar arguments, one can show 
 <disp-formula id="pcbi.1007000.e005" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1007000.e005.jpg" id="pcbi.1007000.e005g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M5" class="math">
    <mtable displaystyle="true" class="mtable">
     <mtr class="mtr">
      <mtd columnalign="right" class="mtd">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <msub class="msub">
         <mi class="mi">r</mi>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">M</mi>
          <mo class="mo">→</mo>
          <mi class="mi">N</mi>
         </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo class="mo">=</mo>
        <mi class="mi">κ</mi>
        <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width="2pt" class="mspace"/>
        <mtext class="mtext">max</mtext>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">{</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">e</mi>
          <mi class="mi">N</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">e</mi>
          <mi class="mi">M</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">,</mo>
         <mn class="mn">0</mn>
         <mo class="mo">}</mo>
        </mrow>
       </mrow>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
    </mtable>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(4)</label>
 </disp-formula> and so the net rate of change in mitigators is 
 <disp-formula id="pcbi.1007000.e006" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1007000.e006.jpg" id="pcbi.1007000.e006g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M6" class="math">
    <mtable displaystyle="true" class="mtable">
     <mtr class="mtr">
      <mtd columnalign="right" class="mtd">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mfrac class="mfrac">
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">d</mi>
          <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         </mrow>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">d</mi>
          <mi class="mi">t</mi>
         </mrow>
        </mfrac>
        <mo class="mo">=</mo>
        <msub class="msub">
         <mi class="mi">r</mi>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">N</mi>
          <mo class="mo">→</mo>
          <mi class="mi">M</mi>
         </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo class="mo">−</mo>
        <msub class="msub">
         <mi class="mi">r</mi>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">M</mi>
          <mo class="mo">→</mo>
          <mi class="mi">N</mi>
         </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo class="mo">=</mo>
        <mi class="mi">κ</mi>
        <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">e</mi>
          <mi class="mi">M</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">e</mi>
          <mi class="mi">N</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">,</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
    </mtable>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(5)</label>
 </disp-formula> which has an equivalent form to the replicator equations of evolutionary game theory [
 <xref rid="pcbi.1007000.ref032" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">32</xref>]. Writing the payoff functions explicitly gives 
 <disp-formula id="pcbi.1007000.e007" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1007000.e007.jpg" id="pcbi.1007000.e007g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M7" class="math">
    <mtable displaystyle="true" class="mtable">
     <mtr class="mtr">
      <mtd columnalign="right" class="mtd">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mfrac class="mfrac">
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">d</mi>
          <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         </mrow>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">d</mi>
          <mi class="mi">t</mi>
         </mrow>
        </mfrac>
        <mo class="mo">=</mo>
        <mi class="mi">κ</mi>
        <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">[</mo>
        <mi class="mi">γ</mi>
        <mo class="mo">−</mo>
        <mi class="mi">α</mi>
        <mo class="mo">+</mo>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <mi class="mi">c</mi>
         <mo class="mo">+</mo>
         <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mover accent="true" class="mover">
         <mi class="mi">f</mi>
         <mo class="mo">˜</mo>
        </mover>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">T</mi>
          <mi class="mi">f</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">+</mo>
        <mi class="mi">δ</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <mn class="mn">2</mn>
         <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">]</mo>
        <mo class="mo">,</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
    </mtable>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(6)</label>
 </disp-formula> which can be reduced to 
 <disp-formula id="pcbi.1007000.e008" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1007000.e008.jpg" id="pcbi.1007000.e008g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M8" class="math">
    <mtable displaystyle="true" class="mtable">
     <mtr class="mtr">
      <mtd columnalign="right" class="mtd">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mfrac class="mfrac">
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">d</mi>
          <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         </mrow>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">d</mi>
          <mi class="mi">t</mi>
         </mrow>
        </mfrac>
        <mo class="mo">=</mo>
        <mi class="mi">κ</mi>
        <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">[</mo>
        <mo class="mo">−</mo>
        <mi class="mi">β</mi>
        <mo class="mo">+</mo>
        <mi class="mi">f</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">T</mi>
          <mi class="mi">f</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">+</mo>
        <mi class="mi">δ</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <mn class="mn">2</mn>
         <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">]</mo>
        <mo class="mo">,</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
    </mtable>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(7)</label>
 </disp-formula> by introducing the new parameter 
 <italic class="italic">β</italic> = 
 <italic class="italic">α</italic> − 
 <italic class="italic">γ</italic> (the net cost to mitigate) scaled function 
 <inline-formula id="pcbi.1007000.e009" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1007000.e009.jpg" id="pcbi.1007000.e009g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M9" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">f</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">(</mo>
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">(</mo>
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
      <mo class="mo">+</mo>
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
      <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mover accent="true" class="mover">
      <mi class="mi">f</mi>
      <mo class="mo">˜</mo>
     </mover>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">(</mo>
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> (the net temperature associated gain to mitigate).
</p>
